    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 1 vs. required level 2) is offset by the strength of evidence across all other factors, the direct relevance of the single tested condition to the intended COU, and the conservative acceptance bounds applied to output comparison. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level determination for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending FEA framework.",
